@page "/roadmap"
<SeoHead Title="Roadmap" Description="Completed, current and planned LifeOS product tracks." CanonicalPath="/roadmap" />
<PageIntro Eyebrow="Roadmap" Title="Build the public foundation before the next shell." Summary="The sequence preserves product boundaries: Website foundation, documentation extraction, simplified Desktop shell, module migration, contextual systems and v8 release polish." />
<section class="page-shell section"><div class="roadmap-list"><article class="complete"><span>COMPLETE</span><div><small>Desktop</small><h2>v7 beta baseline</h2><p>Core operating environment, validation and release checkpoint closed.</p></div></article><article class="complete"><span>COMPLETE</span><div><small>Mobile Companion</small><h2>v0.1 beta baseline</h2><p>Lightweight capture, glance, review, outbox and send-to-desktop track closed.</p></div></article><article class="current"><span>CURRENT</span><div><small>Website · Group 40</small><h2>Public foundation</h2><p>Information architecture, design identity, first content, docs shell, evidence and honest early-access state.</p></div></article><article><span>NEXT</span><div><small>Website + Desktop</small><h2>Documentation extraction</h2><p>Move long system explanations to the Website while preserving contextual help inside Desktop.</p></div></article><article><span>PLANNED</span><div><small>Desktop v8</small><h2>Simplified shell and module migration</h2><p>Carry the shared design language into Desktop after the public foundation is proven.</p></div></article><article><span>FUTURE</span><div><small>Separate product</small><h2>Full Mobile</h2><p>A broader mobile app on its own product purpose, codebase and release track.</p></div></article></div></section>
